rComments: A pleasant gentleman with a delightful sense of humour! Even though his lectures are more or less just spoken versions of the textbook, I always enjoy the logic puzzles that he puts up. I also reall love the subtle mischief that he speaks with; really shows how much he enjoys what he's doing! The course was very interesting and an easy GPA booster.

Never really went to lectures but can still do great from reading lecture slides. he is caring and will give you great feedback if you show him ur essay before hand. his exams are very fair. they are straight from his lecture slides. great prof and such a cutie. lectures were kind of boring since he talked quietly but he made jokes and it was good
Lovely introduction to philosophy. Still one of my favourite moments in university, reflecting back after a few years.
Cool guy, relatively funny. Lectures get a little boring though. The content is fun to learn when you are learning though.
Amazing professor of philosophy!!

I am a neuroscience and mental health major and just wanted to take some electives for my last semester before I graduate.. who knew I LOVE philosiphy! This was one of my favourite courses I have taken at UTSC! Prof Seager is great! Read the book and go to class (because his lectures are great) and you'll do well.. speaking from experience :)
Professor Seager is one of those professors that students respect and adore. He ties in Philosophy with recent events that our generation can relate to and most importantly, he does it with humor.

You could probably go to NO class and still do fine in the course. It is VERY textbook based. This semester we talked about causation and it was one of the most boring classes I have ever took. He seems very passionate and very intelligent nonetheless. Also , it is not a very hard course, provided that you are willing to fight to stay awake in it.
This prof knows what he is talking about and presents his material and a captive manner. I used to like philosophy, but he really ignited my passion for it. Class act.

His classes are only easy if you do the assignments and actually bother to read the book. I think he's incredibly interesting to listen to, but his lectures are not really required to do well in the class. Awesome prof though! Would definitely recommend him over anyone else at the university.

He is very excited about his class and that makes him a joy to watch. He does not say much about how his tests will be but the midterm if you read the book and read the questions right was easy. You will have to write 2 essays i suggest paying attention to what your TA says and if you can see him in his office. very fast in  email reply as well.
DO NOT PASS THIS PROF UP!!! You will love him!!! He is such a nice guy and very intelligent...he will make you love philosophy.
Really great professor. Is really interested in the subject. And is adorable and so intensely into what he's talking about. Made me LOVE logic and metaphysics.
Adorable prof. Really interested in his subject, so its so great to see how excited he is! And he definitely makes concepts straightforward and very clear. Made me appreciate logic!
A really fair professor who teaches completely from the book. I thought his lectures were pretty useless but are not bad if you need further clarification. His exams are really fair which is nice!
Good class. I enjoyed it. He was a good professor and I would recommend this class even if you need an elective.
Not a bad prof. His lessons are straight from the textbook but he does clarify a lot of the concepts very well.

seager!! i think the best thing about him is the fact that he looks like what i imagine aristotle would have looked like, but other than that, the guy reads right out of the book, so theres really no reason to go to class. But then again it is A10 with like 300 students
He is totally awesome, my favourite philosophy prof by far.
lectures aren't very useful! do the excercise like crazy! mid-terms are ok, but you will have to write real fast!
Awesome course... he is like the ultimate philosopher with his beard

He's a good prof and very helpful in his office hours. You can go talk to him about doubts and questions. Loved his lectures, very interesting and informative. He's funny sometimes and makes phil so interesting..sometimes has slides to show. Knows what he is talking about.
lectures were interesting, but watch out for that final exam, marks go way down!

Prof. Seager's a great prof. I actually ended up loving Symbolic Logic because of him. He's got a knack for explaining complex ideas simply and eloquently. And I've never had another prof who was as available for the students as he was.
BEST DAMN PHILOSOPHY PROF ALIVE
best prof i had as an undergrad.  seager, i love you!
Friendly, knowledgeable, and enthusiastic
